TowerDefense

Class Tile

  • java.lang.Object
    • Engine.GameObject
      • TowerDefense.Tile

  • public class Tile
extends Engine.GameObject
    A tile is a rectangular area representing terrain on a 2-dimensional grid. This grid is the Grid. As you might expect, the Tile class and Grid class are quite coupled.
    Author:
    Branden Drake, Rachel Horton

        exit0 - One direction that the path exits from this tile.
        exit1 - The other direction that the path exits from this tile.
        pathImage - The Path image to use if drawing this tile.
        Returns:
        True if the path was created.

      • pathConnectsTo

        public boolean pathConnectsTo(Direction direction)
        Returns true if this Tile is capable of connecting to form part of a Path with the Tile in the specified direction. Specifically, if this Tile branches in the specified direction, and the Tile in that direction branches in the opposite direction, returns true.
        Parameters:
        direction - The direction to check.
        Returns:
        True if this Tile and the Tile in the specified direction are ready to form a Path.

      • pathConnectsUp

      • pathBranchesWithoutConnectingTo

        public boolean pathBranchesWithoutConnectingTo(Direction direction)
        Returns true if this Tile branches in a direction, but the Tile in that direction (if any) doesn't branch in our direction. This means that the two Tiles cannot connect as part of a Path.
        Parameters:
        direction - The direction to check in.
        Returns:
        True if the two Tiles branch in opposite directions.
